The supplemental consolidated report, prepared by the Trump Administration in accordance with the War Powers Resolution, provides an update on the deployments of the United States Armed Forces equipped for combat. The report highlights the ongoing military operations in support of US counterterrorism efforts, including the fight against al-Qa'ida, the Taliban, and ISIS. It mentions deployments in Afghanistan, Iraq, Syria, Yemen, Jordan, Lebanon, Turkey, East Africa, Libya, the Lake Chad Basin and Sahel Region, Cuba, the Philippines, and Egypt. The report also mentions the military operations in Syria, specifically the strikes conducted in response to the Syrian government's use of chemical weapons. Additionally, it mentions the United States' participation in the Multinational Force and Observers in Egypt, as well as its contribution to the Kosovo Force in Kosovo. The report asserts that these operations are conducted under the President's constitutional and statutory authority as Commander in Chief and Chief Executive.